HEADWORD: Hetman
<hw>Het"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Hetmans</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Pol. <ets>hetman</ets>. Cf.
<er>Ataman</er>.]</ety> <def>A Cossack headman or general. The title of
<xex>chief hetman</xex> is now held by the heir to the throne of
Russia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

